  <h2><a href="/articles/2006/05/23/link-new-graphs-for-gruff">Link: New Graphs for Gruff</a></h2>
<p class="auth">Posted by kev
<span class="typo_date" title="Tue, 23 May 2006 15:53:00 GMT">Tue, 23 May 2006 15:53:00 GMT</span></p>
<p><strong>Update</strong>: Sorry, this isn&#8217;t an update to Gruff, but an update to the CSS Graphs helper. Thanks <a href="http://cwilliams.textdriven.com/articles/2006/05/25/css-graphs-plugin-patch">Chris</a>.</p>

<p><a href="http://nubyonrails.com">Geoff Grosenbach</a> of <a href="http://podcast.rubyonrails.com">Rails Podcast</a> fame is <a href="http://nubyonrails.com/articles/2006/05/23/css-graphs-update-new-graph-types">updating Gruff</a>, the excellent graphing library.</p>

<p><a href="http://nubyonrails.com/pages/gruff">Gruff</a> is easy to <a href="http://nubyonrails.com/pages/gruff">use</a> and <a href="http://glu.ttono.us/articles/2006/03/29/spiders-invade-gruff-graphs">extend</a>,
and makes really beautiful graphs.</p>

<p>Go check it out.</p>

<p><img src="http://thar.be/spider_small.png" alt="Spider Graph"/></p>

  
  <p class="meta">Posted in <a href="/articles/category/ruby" rel="tag">Ruby</a>, <a href="/articles/category/sightings" rel="tag">sightings</a></p>
